Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.65,0:00:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Our world is filled with breathtaking beauty.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.20,0:00:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did God create the earth \Nin such a special way?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.37,0:00:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Even from space, \Nit stands alone as wonderfully unique.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.50,0:00:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,God created the earth \Nwith an abundance of water.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.47,0:00:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He placed it \Nat just the right distance from the sun \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.35,0:00:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and set its rotation at just the right speed.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.98,0:00:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He gave it a moon \Nto stabilize the earth’s tilt, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.53,0:00:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,contributing to consistent seasons.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.99,0:01:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And he created \Nan amazing variety of living creatures \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.50,0:01:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to share the earth with.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.87,0:01:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did God put forth so much effort \Nto create this beautiful earth?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.38,0:01:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he wanted to give \Nthe first human couple, Adam and Eve, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.64,0:01:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,a wonderful home.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.64,0:01:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as they obeyed God, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.85,0:01:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,they and their children would live forever \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.44,0:01:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and expand the Paradise garden \Nto cover the entire globe.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.57,0:01:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,This was God’s purpose for the earth.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.86,0:01:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So what happened? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.24,0:01:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Why isn’t the earth a paradise?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.24,0:01:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Sadly, Adam and Eve chose to disobey God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.25,0:01:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They eventually grew old and died. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.63,0:01:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Paradise was lost. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.05,0:01:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But did this mean that God’s original purpose \Nfor the earth had changed?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.30,0:01:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine that a father decides to build \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.43,0:02:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,a beautiful home for his son.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.31,0:02:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He gives it to him as a gift. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.19,0:02:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But instead of being thankful, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.18,0:02:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the son neglects his father’s gift \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.19,0:02:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and the house falls into disrepair.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.62,0:02:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What would a loving father do? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.54,0:02:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Would he destroy the house \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.71,0:02:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and all his hard work?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.92,0:02:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,No, he would patiently save it \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.88,0:02:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for a family member who would appreciate it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.89,0:02:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,In a similar way, \Nalthough Adam rejected the gift, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.94,0:02:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the Bible tells us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.94,0:02:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,that God didn’t change \Nhis purpose for the earth.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.99,0:02:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,His purpose still stands. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.16,0:03:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants to give this gift, \Nan earth-wide paradise, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.45,0:03:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to you to enjoy \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.12,0:03:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,in happiness and health forever!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.79,0:03:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You may wonder: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.13,0:03:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,‘How will Paradise be restored? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.01,0:03:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And who will live there?’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.34,0:03:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Those questions are answered in lesson 5 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.84,0:03:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of the brochure Good News From God!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.31,0:03:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You can download a copy from jw.org.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.23,0:03:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s Witnesses would be happy \Nto study the Bible with you.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.65,0:03:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Fill in the online request for a Bible study, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.82,0:03:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and a Witness in your area \Nwill call to discuss the Bible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.03,0:03:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,at a time and place convenient for you.\N
